ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-3 On December 18, 2001, approximately 1045 mountain standard time, a Piper PA-28-235, N8704W, operated by Cherokee Flyers, LLC, of Grand Junction, Colorado, was substantially damaged when it collided with terrain during landing at Crested Butte, Colorado. 
ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-4 The private pilot and two passengers were not injured. 
ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-5 Visual meteorological conditions prevailed, and no flight plan had been filed for the personal flight being conducted under Title 14 CFR Part 91. 
ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-6 The flight originated in Grand Junction at 1000. 
ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-7 According to the pilot, he landed on runway 29 and the airplane began veering off to the left. 
ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-8 The pilot applied right rudder but to no avail The airplane collided with a snow bank on the south side of the runway, and the nose landing gear collapsed. 
ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-9 The fuselage was also buckled. 
ntsb4173txt-1-5-5-0-10 The pilot said that after walking along the runway and locating the point of touch down, he noted a skid mark made by the left wheel and he suspected the brake may have locked. 
